<subSubSection id="B799E670D60D0845006F6AE6543F88C9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="taxonomic remarks">
<paragraph id="92E001F54ED3155414E653166C03D571" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Taxonomic remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7F39A3DC1623DF205A2FD7313E61968F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species is most similar in general appearance to 
<taxonomicName id="0A8EF07803EF7182D9A4C68ADE3FB1F5" genus="P." lsidName="P. ryukyuensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="ryukyuensis">
<emphasis id="E5370D6742691EDE982CEBC787433482" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. ryukyuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
among the named species known from East and Southeast Asia (for details, see under Taxonomic remarks of &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="47892A7CC00A24F33153227BDAD73427" genus="P." lsidName="P. ryukyuensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="ryukyuensis">
<emphasis id="5D7032AC2E79A565C698B389D1E17365" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. ryukyuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CBDD8F4D82028209E1305F0FE20BFF4F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="17F7C8C61C116DC688C301ECE5BC71B6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
